target_title: Wrong keyboard layout in macOS client

note.body:
I have the same problem but when connecting from `GNOME 47.2 (Wayland)` on `Manjaro Linux x86_64` with `Linux 6.12.4-1-MANJARO` kernel to another machine on my LAN with the same specs; `GNOME 47.2 (Wayland)` on `Manjaro Linux x86_64` with `Linux 6.12.4-1-MANJARO`.

Both machines have `LANG=en_US.UTF-8 locale` and keyboard layout `ch` configured.

The keyboard layout that I get when connecting via GNOME Connections seems like gibberish, nothing makes sense.

target_title: Keyboard doesn't work in full screen

note.body:
Hi Jhon,

thank you for this report. The cause of the issue was that fullscreen/unfullscreen buttons were stealing focus once they were clicked. Setting the handy property "focus-on-click" to "False" fixes this issue.
